15#ifndef DST_RESULT_H
16#define DST_RESULT_H 1
17
18/*! \file dst/result.h */
19
20#include <isc/lang.h>
21#include <isc/resultclass.h>
22
23/*
24 * Nothing in this file truly depends on <isc/result.h>, but the
25 * DST result codes are considered to be publicly derived from
26 * the ISC result codes, so including this file buys you the ISC_R_
27 * namespace too.
28 */
29#include <isc/result.h> /* Contractual promise. */
30
31#define DST_R_UNSUPPORTEDALG (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 0)
32#define DST_R_CRYPTOFAILURE (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 1)
33/* compat */
34#define DST_R_OPENSSLFAILURE DST_R_CRYPTOFAILURE
35#define DST_R_NOCRYPTO (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 2)
36#define DST_R_NULLKEY (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 3)
37#define DST_R_INVALIDPUBLICKEY (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 4)
38#define DST_R_INVALIDPRIVATEKEY (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 5)
39/* 6 is unused */
40#define DST_R_WRITEERROR (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 7)
41#define DST_R_INVALIDPARAM (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 8)
42/* 9 is unused */
43/* 10 is unused */
44#define DST_R_SIGNFAILURE (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 11)
45/* 12 is unused */
46/* 13 is unused */
47#define DST_R_VERIFYFAILURE (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 14)
48#define DST_R_NOTPUBLICKEY (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 15)
49#define DST_R_NOTPRIVATEKEY (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 16)
50#define DST_R_KEYCANNOTCOMPUTESECRET (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 17)
51#define DST_R_COMPUTESECRETFAILURE (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 18)
52#define DST_R_NORANDOMNESS (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 19)
53#define DST_R_BADKEYTYPE (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 20)
54#define DST_R_NOENGINE (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 21)
55#define DST_R_EXTERNALKEY (ISC_RESULTCLASS_DST + 22)
56
57#define DST_R_NRESULTS 23 /* Number of results */
58
59ISC_LANG_BEGINDECLS
60
61const char *
62dst_result_totext(isc_result_t);
63
64void
65dst_result_register(void);
66
67ISC_LANG_ENDDECLS
68
69#endif /* DST_RESULT_H */
